  "text": " One pattern I keep running into when the gut protocol is already right. Client has done the work, elimination diet, clean protein, right binders, right probiotics. Six months in, and the gut symptoms still show up. Bloting after meals that shouldn't cause bloating. Stool that keeps shifting, intermittent reactivity to foods that used to be fine. The thing I check next is the gut lining itself. The layer everything has to pass through. If the epithelium is chronically inflamed, nothing you add downstream clears the pattern. The body keeps opening tight junctions. Food particles keep triggering the immune layer. The microbiome keeps getting disrupted before it can stabilize. There's a peptide that has been studied for mecosyl repair specifically. BPC157, short chain, body protection compound. In practice, I use the delayed release oral form from InfinoWell. Penta decapeptide that may support the tight junction reset. The rest of the protocol is waiting on. Most gut protocols assume the lining is intact. When it isn't, every input reaches a closed door, not a replacement for the protocol. The floor of the protocol is standing on. Full pattern breakdown at tr.eslash.owq7fm. Type it.",
